Docker compose

1. Rename .env.example to .env
2. Edit .env to replace public and private with your public and private keys from Marvel API
3. Run docker-compose up --build ( you may omit --build if you didn't change code from last launch)
4. Open http://localhost:8080/spider-man there should be json response with relevant information


Docker

1. Rename Dockerfile.standalone to docker
2. Edit Dockerfile by placing public and private keys in relevant environmental variables
3. Build Docker image and run container.
